<!-- Rename this file to CLAUDE.md to activate it, then build the script from the lesson's PROMPT.md (in the lesson repo's SDD/ folder). -->

# CLAUDE.md — conventions for this rebuild

- Call the model with boto3 Bedrock Converse.
- Model ID + region come from env vars (never hard-coded).
- Load .env with `load_dotenv(find_dotenv())`.
- Keep the Bedrock call in one function so a provider swap is easy.
- Build the prompt as code: a static system prompt + a builder function for the dynamic user prompt.
- Put any data/variable lookups inside the builder; keep rendering pure so it's easy to test.
- Comment only the non-obvious AI/SDK bits — skip the obvious.
- Keep it simple: the shortest code that works.
